{# Narrow drafting context built on the planning step and the boundary dossier. #}
{% if current_chapter is defined %}
{% set active_chapter = current_chapter %}
{% elif chapter is defined %}
{% set active_chapter = chapter %}
{% else %}
{% set active_chapter = "1" %}
{% endif %}
{% set chapter_number = active_chapter | int %}
{% set is_first_chapter = chapter_number == 1 %}
{% set dossier_path = "Story_Dossier_Worksheet.boundaries.md" %}
{% set dossier = dossier_path | doc %}
{% set chapter_start = "[chapter_" ~ active_chapter ~ "]" %}
{% set chapter_end = "[/chapter_" ~ active_chapter ~ "]" %}
{% set voice_rules = dossier | extract_section(start="[authorial_style_and_voice]", end="[/authorial_style_and_voice]") | trim %}
{% set project_overview = dossier | extract_section(start="[project_overview]", end="[/project_overview]") | trim %}
{% set chapter_outline = dossier | extract_section(start=chapter_start, end=chapter_end) | trim %}
{% set plan_path = "plan-chapter-" ~ active_chapter ~ ".md" %}
{% set plan = plan_path | doc %}
{% if chapter_number <= 3 %}
{% set rolling_chapter_start = 1 %}
{% else %}
{% set rolling_chapter_start = chapter_number - 2 %}
{% endif %}

You are writing Chapter {{ active_chapter }} of a commercial firefighter second-chance romance.

You are writing final-feeling prose for a human author to refine, not an outline and not commentary.

Rules:

- Follow the chapter plan exactly.
- Write only chapter prose. No notes, labels, commentary, or scene headers unless the plan explicitly requires them.
- Stay in third-person limited, past tense, and the assigned POV.
- Let emotion appear through action, sensation, dialogue choice, and environmental interaction.
- Use firefighter terminology and the physical world of the station, calls, and gear as part of the prose texture.
- Do not restate emotional beats already proven in prior chapters.
- Every scene must shift leverage, trust, danger, intimacy, or information.
- Do not add scenes, reorder scenes, or introduce off-plan twists.

[Authorial Style and Voice]

{{ voice_rules }}

[/Authorial Style and Voice]

[Project Overview]

{{ project_overview }}

[/Project Overview]

[Current Chapter Outline]

{{ chapter_outline }}

[/Current Chapter Outline]

{% if chapter_number > 3 %}[Earlier Chapter Summaries]

{% for i in range(start=1, end=chapter_number - 2) %}
{% set summary_path = "summary-chapter-" ~ i ~ ".md" %}
[Summary Chapter {{ i }}]

{{ summary_path | doc }}

[/Summary Chapter {{ i }}]

{% endfor %}[/Earlier Chapter Summaries]

{% endif %}{% if not is_first_chapter %}[Recent Manuscript Chapters]

{% for i in range(start=rolling_chapter_start, end=chapter_number) %}
{% set chapter_path = "chapter-" ~ i ~ ".md" %}
[Chapter {{ i }}]

{{ chapter_path | doc }}

[/Chapter {{ i }}]

{% endfor %}[/Recent Manuscript Chapters]

{% endif %}[Plan for Chapter {{ active_chapter }}]

{{ plan }}

[/Plan for Chapter {{ active_chapter }}]

Format the response exactly like this:

## Chapter {{ active_chapter }} Draft

Write Chapter {{ active_chapter }} now. Only prose.
